<subSubSection id="8FAA1E8DFFC4FFF7FF6F26E4FC9E8DE8" pageId="87" pageNumber="87" type="description">
<paragraph id="C70F4D06FFC4FFF7FF6F26E4FD9E8CE0" blockId="87.[128,658,1124,1763]" pageId="87" pageNumber="87">
IDENTIFICATION: Descriptions and measurements of 
<taxonomicName id="00B03685FFC4FFF7FF032706FE5D8C10" baseAuthorityName="Peters" baseAuthorityYear="1867" box="[241,470,1300,1323]" class="Mammalia" family="Phyllostomidae" genus="Tonatia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="87" pageNumber="87" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="brasiliense">
<emphasis id="F5C49114FFC4FFF7FF032706FE5D8C10" box="[241,470,1300,1323]" italics="true" pageId="87" pageNumber="87">Tonatia brasiliense</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
from the Guianas and elsewhere can be found in 
<bibRefCitation id="A32130F7FFC4FFF7FDD62723FF5B8C5E" author="Goodwin, G. G." journalOrPublisher="J. Mammal." pageId="87" pageNumber="87" pagination="204 - 209" part="23" refId="ref94213" refString="Goodwin, G. G. 1942. A summary of recognizable species of Tonatia, with descriptions of two new species. J. Mammal. 23: 204 - 209." title="A summary of recognizable species of Tonatia, with descriptions of two new species" type="journal article" year="1942">Goodwin (1942)</bibRefCitation>
, Swanepoel and 
<bibRefCitation id="A32130F7FFC4FFF7FE42275CFD078C5E" author="Genoways, H. H. &amp; S. L. Williams" box="[432,652,1358,1381]" journalOrPublisher="Ann. Carnegie Mus." pageId="87" pageNumber="87" pagination="323 - 335" part="48" refId="ref93773" refString="Genoways, H. H., and S. L. Williams 1979. Records of bats (Mammalia: Chiroptera) from Suriname. Ann. Carnegie Mus. 48: 323 - 335." title="Records of bats (Mammalia: Chiroptera) from Suriname" type="journal article" year="1979">Genoways (1979)</bibRefCitation>
, Genoways and Williams (1984), and 
<bibRefCitation id="A32130F7FFC4FFF7FDCB277EFE728C9B" author="Brosset, A. &amp; P. Charles-Dominique" journalOrPublisher="Mammalia" pageId="87" pageNumber="87" pagination="509 - 559" part="54" refId="ref91807" refString="Brosset, A., and P. Charles-Dominique 1990. The bats from French Guiana: a taxonomic, faunistic and ecological approach. Mammalia 54: 509 - 559." title="The bats from French Guiana: a taxonomic, faunistic and ecological approach" type="journal article" year="1990">Brosset and Charles­Dominique (1990)</bibRefCitation>
. No subspecies are currently recognized (Genoways and Williams, 1984; Koopman, 1994).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="C70F4D06FFC4FFF7FF6F27F3FB5A88E3" blockId="87.[128,658,1124,1763]" lastBlockId="87.[704,1233,214,1381]" pageId="87" pageNumber="87">
As the smallest member of its genus, 
<taxonomicName id="00B03685FFC4FFF7FDAB27F3FEBD8F2D" baseAuthorityName="Peters" baseAuthorityYear="1867" class="Mammalia" family="Phyllostomidae" genus="Tonatia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="87" pageNumber="87" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="brasiliense">
<emphasis id="F5C49114FFC4FFF7FDAB27F3FEBD8F2D" italics="true" pageId="87" pageNumber="87">Tonatia brasiliense</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is most likely to be confused with species of 
<taxonomicName id="00B03685FFC4FFF7FEC5240EFE518F08" box="[311,474,1564,1587]" class="Mammalia" family="Phyllostomidae" genus="Micronycteris" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="87" pageNumber="87" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="F5C49114FFC4FFF7FEC5240EFE518F08" box="[311,474,1564,1587]" italics="true" pageId="87" pageNumber="87">Micronycteris</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, which are also small gray­brown phyllostomines with large, rounded ears. Genoways and Williams (1984) mentioned several craniodental characters that can be used to distinguish these taxa, but failed to note one obvious external character: whereas all species of 
<emphasis id="F5C49114FFC4FFF7FDEA24DEFD7F89D5" box="[536,756,215,1763]" italics="true" pageId="87" pageNumber="87">Micronyc­ teris</emphasis>
have a pair of large dermal pads forming a ‘‘V’’ on the tip of the chin, the tip of the chin in 
<taxonomicName id="00B03685FFC4FFF7FCBC2303FC7A8813" baseAuthorityName="Peters" baseAuthorityYear="1867" box="[846,1009,273,296]" class="Mammalia" family="Phyllostomidae" genus="Tonatia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="87" pageNumber="87" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="brasiliense">
<emphasis id="F5C49114FFC4FFF7FCBC2303FCD58813" box="[846,862,273,296]" italics="true" pageId="87" pageNumber="87">T</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis id="F5C49114FFC4FFF7FC832303FC7A8813" box="[881,1009,273,296]" italics="true" pageId="87" pageNumber="87">brasiliense</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(and other congeners) has a U­shaped row of tiny dermal papillae (
<bibRefCitation id="A32130F7FFC4FFF7FCE4235EFC5B8858" author="Emmons, L. H." box="[790,976,332,355]" journalOrPublisher="Chicago: Univ. Chicago Press" pageId="87" pageNumber="87" refId="ref92899" refString="Emmons, L. H. 1990. Neotropical rainforest mammals: a field guide. Chicago: Univ. Chicago Press." title="Neotropical rainforest mammals: a field guide" type="book" year="1990">Emmons, 1990</bibRefCitation>
, 1997). We also observed that 
<taxonomicName id="00B03685FFC4FFF7FCBF237BFC6488BB" baseAuthorityName="Peters" baseAuthorityYear="1867" box="[845,1007,361,384]" class="Mammalia" family="Phyllostomidae" genus="Tonatia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="87" pageNumber="87" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="brasiliense">
<emphasis id="F5C49114FFC4FFF7FCBF237BFCD688BB" box="[845,861,361,384]" italics="true" pageId="87" pageNumber="87">T</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis id="F5C49114FFC4FFF7FC9D237BFC6488BB" box="[879,1007,361,384]" italics="true" pageId="87" pageNumber="87">brasiliense</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
folds its ears back against the crown of the head when touched, a behavior seen in several other species of 
<taxonomicName id="00B03685FFC4FFF7FD3223D3FC9188E3" box="[704,794,449,472]" class="Mammalia" family="Phyllostomidae" genus="Tonatia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="87" pageNumber="87" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="F5C49114FFC4FFF7FD3223D3FC9188E3" box="[704,794,449,472]" italics="true" pageId="87" pageNumber="87">Tonatia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(see below) but not in 
<taxonomicName id="00B03685FFC4FFF7FBD523D3FB4188E3" box="[1063,1226,449,472]" class="Mammalia" family="Phyllostomidae" genus="Micronycteris" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="87" pageNumber="87" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="F5C49114FFC4FFF7FBD523D3FB4188E3" box="[1063,1226,449,472]" italics="true" pageId="87" pageNumber="87">Micronycteris</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="C70F4D06FFC4FFF7FD2F23CCFC848A20" blockId="87.[704,1233,214,1381]" pageId="87" pageNumber="87">
Our voucher material conforms closely with previous descriptions of 
<taxonomicName id="00B03685FFC4FFF7FBD423EEFC8F8B0B" baseAuthorityName="Peters" baseAuthorityYear="1867" class="Mammalia" family="Phyllostomidae" genus="Tonatia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="87" pageNumber="87" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="brasiliense">
<emphasis id="F5C49114FFC4FFF7FBD423EEFC8F8B0B" italics="true" pageId="87" pageNumber="87">Tonatia brasiliense</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, particularly those based on material from the Guianas. Probably because our series contains more individuals than do earlier collections from the region, it exhibits somewhat greater size variability than previously reported. However, measurements of our specimens fall within the range of variation previously documented for the species as a whole.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="C70F4D06FFC4FFF7FD2F2133FC9E8DE8" blockId="87.[704,1233,214,1381]" pageId="87" pageNumber="87">
As remarked by Genoways and Williams (1984), 
<taxonomicName id="00B03685FFC4FFF7FCED212DFB8F8A6D" baseAuthorityName="Peters" baseAuthorityYear="1867" box="[799,1028,831,854]" class="Mammalia" family="Phyllostomidae" genus="Tonatia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="87" pageNumber="87" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="brasiliense">
<emphasis id="F5C49114FFC4FFF7FCED212DFB8F8A6D" box="[799,1028,831,854]" italics="true" pageId="87" pageNumber="87">Tonatia brasiliense</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
as currently recognized may be composite. Should this prove to be the case, comparisons with published measurements (e.g., those in 
<bibRefCitation id="A32130F7FFC4FFF7FB962184FC988AF0" author="Goodwin, G. G." journalOrPublisher="J. Mammal." pageId="87" pageNumber="87" pagination="204 - 209" part="23" refId="ref94213" refString="Goodwin, G. G. 1942. A summary of recognizable species of Tonatia, with descriptions of two new species. J. Mammal. 23: 204 - 209." title="A summary of recognizable species of Tonatia, with descriptions of two new species" type="journal article" year="1942">Goodwin [1942]</bibRefCitation>
and Swanepoel and 
<bibRefCitation id="A32130F7FFC4FFF7FBBC21A6FC858AD3" author="Genoways, H. H. &amp; S. L. Williams" journalOrPublisher="Ann. Carnegie Mus." pageId="87" pageNumber="87" pagination="323 - 335" part="48" refId="ref93773" refString="Genoways, H. H., and S. L. Williams 1979. Records of bats (Mammalia: Chiroptera) from Suriname. Ann. Carnegie Mus. 48: 323 - 335." title="Records of bats (Mammalia: Chiroptera) from Suriname" type="journal article" year="1979">Genoways [1979]</bibRefCitation>
) suggest that our specimens, along with others from the Guianas, would be referred to 
<taxonomicName id="00B03685FFC4FFF7FCC7261EFC538D18" baseAuthorityName="Peters" baseAuthorityYear="1867" box="[821,984,1036,1059]" class="Mammalia" family="Phyllostomidae" genus="Tonatia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="87" pageNumber="87" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="brasiliense">
<emphasis id="F5C49114FFC4FFF7FCC7261EFCCE8D18" box="[821,837,1036,1059]" italics="true" pageId="87" pageNumber="87">T</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis id="F5C49114FFC4FFF7FCAA261EFC538D18" box="[856,984,1036,1059]" italics="true" pageId="87" pageNumber="87">brasiliense</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
rather than to other taxa currently treated as synonyms (e.g., 
<taxonomicName id="00B03685FFC4FFF7FB69263BFD6E8D65" class="Mammalia" family="Phyllostomidae" genus="Micronycteris" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="87" pageNumber="87" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="minuta">
<emphasis id="F5C49114FFC4FFF7FB69263BFD6E8D65" italics="true" pageId="87" pageNumber="87">minuta</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<emphasis id="F5C49114FFC4FFF7FD0C2655FC098D65" box="[766,898,1095,1118]" italics="true" pageId="87" pageNumber="87">nicaraguae</emphasis>
, and 
<emphasis id="F5C49114FFC4FFF7FC242655FBDE8D65" box="[982,1109,1095,1118]" italics="true" pageId="87" pageNumber="87">venezuelae</emphasis>
; Handley [1966], Gardner [1976], 
<bibRefCitation id="A32130F7FFC4FFF7FC0E2676FC848DA3" author="Jones, J. K., Jr. &amp; D. C. Carter" editor="Baker, J. K. &amp; Jones, Jr. &amp; D. C. Carter" journalOrPublisher="Biology of bats of the New World family Phyllostomidae, pt. 1: 7 - 38. Spec. Publ. Mus. Texas Tech Univ." pageId="87" pageNumber="87" part="10" refId="ref96048" refString="Jones, J. K., Jr., and D. C. Carter 1976. Annotated checklist with keys to subfamilies and genera. In R. J. Baker, J. K. Jones, Jr., and D. C. Carter (eds.), Biology of bats of the New World family Phyllostomidae, pt. 1: 7 - 38. Spec. Publ. Mus. Texas Tech Univ. 10." title="Annotated checklist with keys to subfamilies and genera" type="journal volume" volumeTitle="R. J" year="1976">Jones and Carter [1976]</bibRefCitation>
, Genoways and Williams [1984], 
<bibRefCitation id="A32130F7FFC4FFF7FB522693FC608D8E" author="Medellin, R. A. &amp; H. T. Arita" bookContentInfo="5 pp." journalOrPublisher="Mamm. Species 334" pageId="87" pageNumber="87" refId="ref98027" refString="Medellin, R. A., and H. T. Arita 1989. Tonatia evotis and Tonatia silvicola. Mamm. Species 334: 5 pp." title="Tonatia evotis and Tonatia silvicola" type="book" year="1989">Medellín and Arita [1989]</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation id="A32130F7FFC4FFF7FBF3268CFB408D8E" author="Koopman, K. F." box="[1025,1227,1182,1205]" editor="D. E. Wilson &amp; D. M. Reeder" journalOrPublisher="Washington, DC: Smithson. Inst. Press" pageId="87" pageNumber="87" refId="ref96667" refString="1993. Order Chiroptera. In D. E. Wilson and D. M. Reeder (eds.), Mammal species of the World, a taxonomic and geographic reference, 2 nd ed.: 137 - 241. Washington, DC: Smithson. Inst. Press." title="Order Chiroptera" type="book" volumeTitle="Mammal species of the World, a taxonomic and geographic reference, 2 nd" year="1993">Koopman [1993</bibRefCitation>
, 1994]).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="8FAA1E8DFFC4FFF7FD2F26CBFB828C5E" pageId="87" pageNumber="87" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="C70F4D06FFC4FFF7FD2F26CBFB828C5E" blockId="87.[704,1233,214,1381]" pageId="87" pageNumber="87">
FIELD OBSERVATIONS: All of the nine specimens of 
<taxonomicName id="00B03685FFC4FFF7FCC126E5FB9C8C35" baseAuthorityName="Peters" baseAuthorityYear="1867" box="[819,1047,1271,1294]" class="Mammalia" family="Phyllostomidae" genus="Tonatia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="87" pageNumber="87" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="brasiliense">
<emphasis id="F5C49114FFC4FFF7FCC126E5FB9C8C35" box="[819,1047,1271,1294]" italics="true" pageId="87" pageNumber="87">Tonatia brasiliense</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
that we caught at Paracou were taken in ground­level mistnets: six in swampy primary forest and three in creekside primary forest.
</paragraph>
